The expression of stimuli-responsiveness of complex was further validated through another method. It was reported that polymer chain length has a certain impact on the stimuli-responsive properties of polymers [29]. Taking PNIPAm as an example, there is a critical chain length for the coil-to-globule transition of PNIPAm, which is 15 repeating units (1697 g/mol). The conformation of PNIPAm with chain lengths exceeding 15 repeating units is temperature-dependent [30]. Therefore, the number average molecular weight of CNTs/CDs-PNIPAm was measured with the GPC method to obtain the chain length of PNIPAm (
                        Table S2
                     ). The results indicate that the number average molecular weight of CNTs/CDs-PNIPAm is 2835 g/mol, which is similar to that of PNIPAm (2842 g/mol), indicating similar properties. The chain length of CNTs/CDs-PNIPAm is calculated to be 25.1, which means there are 25 repeating units in PNIPAm chains. Therefore, from the perspective of polymer chain length, it further confirms that the hydrophilicity and hydrophobicity of CNTs/CDs PNIPAm can be regulated by temperature changes.
